parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS module can cause the rear brakes to malfunction, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The rear brake pedal becomes solid or stuck
the rear brakes do not function
the ABS failure light comes on
the bike may pull to one side while braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loss of clutch control can cause the vehicle to stall or shift into neutral unexpectedly, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: clutch pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the compensator assembly can cause problems with starting, leading to riders being stranded, and potentially posing a safety risk due to backfires that can shoot smoke and flames out of the engine.
symptoms: smoke and flames shooting out of the engine
broken teeth in the starting gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle control can cause the vehicle to go into limp mode, leading to a loss of throttle response, which can be particularly dangerous when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
The failure of the fuel filter housing O-ring can cause the engine to shut down without warning, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents.
A fuel system failure can cause a carbon dioxide leak, which can lead to exposure to toxic fumes, driver disorientation, and potential accidents.
